HEADWORD: Bicuspid
<hw>Bi*cus"pid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the
two double-pointed teeth which intervene between the canines (cuspids)
and the molars, on each side of each jaw. See <er>Tooth</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

